WEBVTT

00:02.253 --> 00:03.754
Meredith: THE HARPER AVERY

00:03.754 --> 00:05.176
IS ONE OF THE HIGHEST AWARDS
A SURGEON CAN EARN.

00:05.176 --> 00:07.007
THEY ALWAYS MAKE THE CALLS
TO THE NOMINEES

00:07.007 --> 00:09.050
ON THE SAME FRIDAY
OF THE SAME MONTH

00:09.050 --> 00:12.433
AT 8:00 A.M.
EAST COAST TIME...

00:12.433 --> 00:13.844
5:00 A.M. IN SEATTLE.

00:13.844 --> 00:15.096
[ ALARM BEEPING ]
[ BOTH GASP, SHRIEK ]

00:15.096 --> 00:16.137
CRAP, MER!

00:16.137 --> 00:17.188
OH, MY GOD!
THE PHONE!

00:17.188 --> 00:18.189
OH! MER!
OH! I'M SORRY!

00:18.189 --> 00:19.140
OH, THE PHONE!
NO, THE PHONE.

00:19.140 --> 00:20.771
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.
DID WE REMEMBER TO --

00:20.771 --> 00:22.773
NO, NO, IT'S --
IT'S -- IT'S CHARGED.
OH, GOD!

00:22.773 --> 00:24.905
IT'S -- IT'S CHARGED,
AND THE RINGER'S ON.
[ GROANS ]

00:24.905 --> 00:27.278
OKAY, HOLD ON. YOU GOT TO PUT ON
SOME LIPSTICK. HERE.

00:27.278 --> 00:29.110
MY MOTHER
WAS NOMINATED FIVE TIMES.

00:29.110 --> 00:30.781
I'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS BEFORE.

00:30.781 --> 00:32.153
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT IF --

00:32.153 --> 00:34.995
NO, IT'S NOT POSSIBLE,
BECAUSE CATHERINE AVERY SAID

00:34.995 --> 00:36.537
THAT YOU WERE
ON THE SHORT LIST,

00:36.537 --> 00:39.080
AND YOUR PROJECT IS --
IT'S INNOVATIVE.
UH-HUH.

00:39.080 --> 00:41.662
IT'S GONNA LEAD TO
THE ACTUAL PRINTING OF HEARTS.
UH-HUH.

00:41.662 --> 00:42.963
MILLIONS WILL BE SAVED.

00:42.963 --> 00:44.295
WHAT TIME IS IT?
5:01.

00:44.295 --> 00:45.876
DID THEY?
NOT YET.
[ GROANS ]

00:45.876 --> 00:46.667
DID THEY?
Alex: NO.

00:46.667 --> 00:48.929
OH, GOD!

00:48.929 --> 00:51.472
OKAY, LISTEN,
IF THERE ARE FIVE NOMINEES,

00:51.472 --> 00:52.473
IT'S ALPHABETICAL.

00:52.473 --> 00:53.554
YANG IS LAST.

00:53.554 --> 00:54.805
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

00:54.805 --> 00:55.766
OH!

00:55.766 --> 00:57.017
OH, GEEZ, HAIRBALL!
OH, SORRY!

00:57.017 --> 00:58.349
IT'S SHANE.
WHAT ARE YOU --

00:58.349 --> 01:01.061
HEY. NO. UH, NOT YET,
BUT IT'S STILL EARLY.

01:01.061 --> 01:02.443
IT'S, UH...
5:02.

01:02.443 --> 01:05.896
IF THE PHONE RINGS,
EVERYTHING CHANGES.

01:05.896 --> 01:08.489
SUDDENLY, YOU'RE A SUPERSTAR.
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

01:08.489 --> 01:10.111
IF IT DOESN'T...

01:10.111 --> 01:11.362
I DON'T KNOW.

01:11.362 --> 01:12.953
MY MOM WAS A SUPERSTAR.

01:12.953 --> 01:14.575
SHE ALWAYS GOT THE CALL.

01:14.575 --> 01:17.158
MER, SERIOUSLY,
WHAT IF THEY DON'T CALL?

01:19.039 --> 01:20.040
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

01:20.040 --> 01:21.252
[ ALL SCREAMING ]

01:21.252 --> 01:22.833
OH, MY GOD.
OH, MY GOD.

01:22.833 --> 01:24.255
WHAT DO I DO?
ANSWER IT.

01:24.255 --> 01:26.707
IT'S BOSTON. IT'S BOSTON.
IT'S THEM. IT'S THEM. IT'S THEM.
OKAY.

01:26.707 --> 01:28.419
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
OKAY. OKAY.
[ HUFFS ]

01:28.419 --> 01:31.472
YOU ARE GONNA BE
GRACIOUS AND HUMBLE.

01:31.472 --> 01:33.844
YOU ARE GONNA THANK THEM,
BUT YOU ARE NOT GONNA GROVEL.

01:33.844 --> 01:35.095
YOU REMEMBER
WHO YOU ARE.
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

01:35.095 --> 01:37.218
YOU ARE CRISTINA YANG,

01:37.218 --> 01:38.849
AND YOU ARE GOING TO CHANGE
THE FACE OF MEDICINE.

01:38.849 --> 01:40.311
GO.
JUST ANSWER
THE DAMN PHONE!

01:40.311 --> 01:42.183
OH, SHH! QUIET!
SHH! SHH!

01:42.183 --> 01:42.983
STAY STILL.

01:45.436 --> 01:46.937
HELLO?

01:48.028 --> 01:50.191
YES,
THIS IS CRISTINA YANG.

01:50.191 --> 01:52.693
Stephanie:
HE SAID "WE"?

01:52.693 --> 01:54.945
YOU'RE SURE
SHANE SAID "WE"?

01:54.945 --> 01:57.698
HE SAID,
"DID WE GET THE NOMINATION?"

01:58.829 --> 02:01.622
THE WAY HE SEES IT,
HE AND YANG JUST GOT NOMINATED

02:01.622 --> 02:04.165
FOR THE HIGHEST SURGICAL HONOR
IN THE LAND.

02:04.165 --> 02:05.416
HE'S GONNA BE
INSUFFERABLE NOW.

02:05.416 --> 02:08.008
WE HAVE TO KNOCK HIM DOWN A PEG.
HE'S STILL YOUR SWAP MONKEY.

02:08.008 --> 02:09.800
I CAN'T DO THAT TODAY.
I'M NOT THAT HORRIBLE.

02:09.800 --> 02:10.591
YOU KIND OF ARE.

02:10.591 --> 02:11.382
HEY, FRANKIE.

02:11.382 --> 02:12.383
HEY.

02:15.806 --> 02:17.598
Arizona:
CRISTINA GOT NOMINATED!

02:17.598 --> 02:18.759
THIS IS HER
GETTING THE CALL.

02:18.759 --> 02:19.760
[ CALLIE CHUCKLES ]

02:19.760 --> 02:21.101
SHE'S WEARING LIPSTICK
AT 5:00 A.M.?

02:21.101 --> 02:22.893
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S CUTE.
Arizona: HEY, FRANKIE.

02:22.893 --> 02:24.645
WE GOT A ROUND SOON,
SO DON'T BE LATE.
OKAY.

02:24.645 --> 02:26.106
ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA
GET THESE GUYS INTO DAYCARE,

02:26.106 --> 02:27.107
AND THEN
I'LL SEE YOU AT THE MEG.

02:27.107 --> 02:28.068
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL MEET YOU THERE.

02:28.068 --> 02:29.109
SEE YOU.
YEAH.

02:29.109 --> 02:30.150
YOU GUYS GOT A MEG?

02:30.150 --> 02:31.482
YEAH, IT'S GONNA MAKE
SCREENING CANDIDATES

02:31.482 --> 02:33.113
FOR THE TRIAL
SO MUCH MORE EFFICIENT.

02:33.113 --> 02:34.695
DOESN'T THAT COST
LIKE A JILLION DOLLARS?

02:34.695 --> 02:37.448
YEAH. DEREK WORKING FOR
THE GOVERNMENT HAS ITS PERKS.

02:37.448 --> 02:38.989
OH, YOU WANT
A HARPER AVERY.

02:38.989 --> 02:41.742
UM, I WANT TO MAKE AN AMPUTEE
WALK USING ROBOTICS,

02:41.742 --> 02:44.084
AND IF I WIN A HARPER AVERY
IN THE PROCESS,

02:44.084 --> 02:45.786
I WON'T TURN IT DOWN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:45.786 --> 02:47.288
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL, NOW'S THE TIME.

02:47.288 --> 02:49.340
I MEAN, SOFIA'S ALMOST
IN SCHOOL ALL DAY,

02:49.340 --> 02:51.462
AND THE TIME-CONSUMING
BABY DAYS ARE OVER.

02:51.462 --> 02:52.553
UNLESS THEY'RE NOT.

02:52.553 --> 02:54.134
OH, I SAY WE QUIT
WHILE WE'RE AHEAD.

02:54.134 --> 02:56.096
YEAH. YEAH.
SOFIA'S PRETTY PERFECT.

02:56.096 --> 02:57.007
WHY TEMPT FATE?

02:57.007 --> 02:58.639
YEAH, AND I CAN ACTUALLY
FINALLY HAVE A THOUGHT.

02:58.639 --> 03:00.721
MM. IS THAT THOUGHT
"WHERE'S MY HARPER AVERY?"

03:00.721 --> 03:02.723
OOH. HEY, MAYBE.

03:02.723 --> 03:04.184
OOH. ALL RIGHT.
MAYBE.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.016
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

03:09.069 --> 03:11.442
HEY, FRANKIE.
MORNING, DR. AVERY.

03:11.442 --> 03:14.405
HEY, ARE YOU NAMED AFTER THAT
BIG AWARD -- THE HARPER AVERY?

03:14.405 --> 03:17.197
IT'S ACTUALLY NAMED AFTER ME,
AFTER MY FAMILY.

03:17.197 --> 03:19.700
HOW DID YOU HEAR...
ABOUT --

03:19.700 --> 03:20.491
OKAY.

03:20.491 --> 03:21.782
HEY.

03:21.782 --> 03:24.084
HEY. DID YOU GO HOME?
I MUST HAVE MISSED YOU.

03:24.084 --> 03:26.287
YEAH, I HAD A 14-YEAR-OLD GSW.
IT WAS SO BLOODY.

03:26.287 --> 03:28.999
I FELT NASTY AFTER SURGERY,
SO I WENT HOME TO CHANGE.

03:28.999 --> 03:30.921
[ SIGHS ] COOL NEWS ABOUT YANG,
THOUGH, HUH?

03:30.921 --> 03:32.423
YEAH.

03:32.423 --> 03:33.504
YOU REALLY
DIDN'T KNOW?

03:33.504 --> 03:35.135
I'M TELLING YOU,
THE NOMINATING COMMITTEE

03:35.135 --> 03:37.177
IS TOTALLY SEPARATE
FROM THE FOUNDATION.

03:37.177 --> 03:38.639
I'M JUST LIKE
EVERYBODY ELSE.

03:38.639 --> 03:40.391
HMM.
ONLY WAY HANDSOMER.

03:40.391 --> 03:41.262
MM.

03:41.262 --> 03:43.143
[ DOOR OPENS ]

03:46.267 --> 03:47.558
IS THAT A SWIMSUIT?

03:47.558 --> 03:49.560
YES, I RAN OUT
OF CLEAN UNDERWEAR

03:49.560 --> 03:51.312
AND HAVEN'T HAD A CHANCE
TO DO LAUNDRY.

03:51.312 --> 03:52.813
WHICH IS WHY
YOU SEND IT OUT.

03:52.813 --> 03:55.025
WE HAVE A PERFECTLY GOOD
WASHING MACHINE AT THE HOUSE.

03:55.025 --> 03:56.737
SAYS THE DOCTOR
IN A SPEEDO.

03:56.737 --> 04:00.781
PAYING SOMEONE TO DO
YOUR LAUNDRY IS AN EXTRAVAGANCE.

04:00.781 --> 04:01.992
HOW MUCH
DID THAT COFFEE COST?

04:01.992 --> 04:03.954
UH, 4 BUCKS.

04:03.954 --> 04:06.827
SO, THAT'S LIKE, WHAT,
SIX -- SIX A WEEK?

04:06.827 --> 04:08.629
MM-HMM. CARRY THE...
THAT'S LIKE...
GIVE ME A SECOND.

04:08.629 --> 04:11.922
LIKE $1,000 A YEAR
YOU'RE JUST THROWING AWAY.

04:11.922 --> 04:14.004
IT'S NOT LIKE I'M SPENDING IT
ON HOOKERS OR PRIVATE PLANES.

04:14.004 --> 04:15.296
IT'S A LATTE.

04:15.296 --> 04:18.138
I'M GONNA GET YOU
ONE OF THOSE MILK-FROTHY THINGS.

04:18.138 --> 04:21.091
I'M GONNA TEACH YOU
HOW TO MAKE YOUR OWN LATTE.

04:21.091 --> 04:22.643
WILL YOU DO IT
IN THAT SWIMSUIT?

04:22.643 --> 04:24.305
HMM?
[ CHUCKLES ] STOP.

04:24.305 --> 04:26.767
OKAY, SO, THERE WAS
A GANG SHOOTING LAST NIGHT,

04:26.767 --> 04:28.098
SO THE E.R.'s CRAZY.

04:28.098 --> 04:30.481
AND THAT PREMIE I TOLD YOU
ABOUT -- SHE GAINED 2 OUNCES,

04:30.481 --> 04:32.943
AND THE NURSES ARE LIKE,
"DOESN'T SHE LOOK FAT?"

04:32.943 --> 04:35.396
AND I'M LIKE, "NO, SHE LOOKS
LIKE A NAKED MOLE RAT."

04:35.396 --> 04:37.898
AND, UH, MY DOCTOR
GOT NOMINATED FOR SOME PRIZE,

04:37.898 --> 04:39.450
AND EVERYONE'S
REALLY JEALOUS.

04:39.450 --> 04:40.451
THAT'S COOL.

04:40.451 --> 04:42.323
NOT AS COOL AS THAT.

04:42.323 --> 04:43.243
YEAH.

04:43.243 --> 04:44.705
MY PARENTS TRY
TO DISTRACT ME

04:44.705 --> 04:46.537
FROM THE FACT
THAT I'M TRAPPED IN A BUBBLE.

04:46.537 --> 04:48.579
WELL, AREN'T YOU GETTING
SOME TEST RESULTS BACK TODAY

04:48.579 --> 04:49.790
THAT ARE GONNA
GET YOU OUT?

04:49.790 --> 04:50.711
YEAH.

04:50.711 --> 04:51.712
HERE THEY COME.

04:51.712 --> 04:52.913
COME VISIT ME.

04:52.913 --> 04:56.086
MY BROTHER'S ROOM IS
END OF THE HALL ON THE RIGHT.

04:56.086 --> 04:57.127
WELL, THERE HE IS.

04:57.127 --> 04:58.469
[ Chuckling ]
HEY, BRADIE BUG.

04:58.469 --> 04:59.550
BRADEN.

04:59.550 --> 05:01.382
UP HIGH, CHAMP.
HI, BABY.

05:01.382 --> 05:02.593
MOM,
WHY ARE YOU CRYING?

05:02.593 --> 05:05.185
[ Voice breaking ]
OH, I'M...

05:05.185 --> 05:06.977
I'M NOT.

05:08.228 --> 05:10.100
I'M SORRY. I CAN'T.

05:12.192 --> 05:16.106
UM, UNFORTUNATELY,
YOUR T-CELL COUNT IS STILL ZERO.

05:16.106 --> 05:17.898
Alex: YOUR INFECTION
IS ALMOST CLEARED,

05:17.898 --> 05:20.070
BUT WE WERE HOPING FOR
YOUR T-CELL COUNT TO RESPOND.

05:20.070 --> 05:21.402
I GET IT.

05:21.402 --> 05:23.534
BUT I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY MY MOM'S CRYING.

05:23.534 --> 05:25.826
THERE'S GOT TO BE OTHER STUFF
YOU GUYS CAN TRY.

05:25.826 --> 05:29.159
YOU'RE NOT GONNA MAKE
ME LIVE IN THIS BUBBLE
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

05:29.159 --> 05:30.080
DAD?

05:30.080 --> 05:32.373
UH, IT'S NOT
SO SIMPLE, BUD.

05:32.373 --> 05:35.165
YOUR BODY HAS NO ABILITY
TO FIGHT INFECTION,

05:35.165 --> 05:37.758
AND THE ENZYME'S
NOT WORKING ANYMORE.

05:37.758 --> 05:40.090
BONE-MARROW TRANSPLANTS IN KIDS
WITH SCID CAN BE EFFECTIVE,

05:40.090 --> 05:41.382
SO WE'RE STILL LOOKING
FOR A MATCH.

05:41.382 --> 05:43.724
THEY'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR A MATCH
FOR ME SINCE I WAS A BABY,

05:43.724 --> 05:44.805
AND THEY HAVEN'T FOUND ONE.

05:44.805 --> 05:46.136
WHAT IF YOU STILL CAN'T?

05:49.430 --> 05:52.603
NO OTHER TREATMENT
FOR YOUR DISEASE EXISTS.

05:52.603 --> 05:57.438
WE'RE WORKING ON IT,
BUT FOR THE TIME BEING...

05:57.438 --> 06:00.691
YOUR ONLY SAFE PLACE
IS RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE.

06:07.077 --> 06:08.489
HEY, FRANKIE.
YOU'RE LATE.

06:08.489 --> 06:10.991
I'M NOT A PATIENT ANYMORE,
SO I DON'T HAVE TO BE AT ROUNDS.

06:10.991 --> 06:12.082
BUT YOU DO.

06:12.082 --> 06:13.754
OH. YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M LATE.

06:13.754 --> 06:15.416
WANT TO RACE?
YEAH. COME ON.

06:15.416 --> 06:17.087
OH, OH, OH!
I GOT YOU!

06:17.087 --> 06:18.419
COME ON! COME ON!

06:18.419 --> 06:19.590
HEY, HEY!
Woman: SLOW DOWN!

06:19.590 --> 06:21.462
THAT'S NOT FAIR!
COME ON!

06:23.464 --> 06:25.175
HEY, LINKIE.

06:25.175 --> 06:27.177
I GOT YOU A CHOCOLATE-
CHIP MUFFIN FOR WHEN
YOU'RE FEELING BETTER.

06:27.177 --> 06:28.679
Cristina: WELL,
HOW ARE YOU FEELING, FRANKIE?

06:28.679 --> 06:30.641
WELL, SHE JUST BEAT ME
IN A RACE, SO...

06:30.641 --> 06:33.063
OH, LOOKS LIKE THAT PACEMAKER
I PUT IN IS WORKING.

06:33.063 --> 06:34.104
AND IV--

06:34.104 --> 06:35.476
SERIOUSLY, IVY.

06:35.476 --> 06:38.148
SOUR-CREAM-AND-ONION CHIPS
FOR BREAKFAST?

06:38.148 --> 06:39.229
YOU SAID
I SHOULD PUT ON WEIGHT.

06:39.229 --> 06:40.571
MMM. GOOD.

06:42.112 --> 06:43.984
Arizona: SO, TWO WEEKS
POST-OP HEART TRANSPLANT,

06:43.984 --> 06:45.986
AND IVY'S INDICES
ARE EXCELLENT.

06:45.986 --> 06:47.578
AND MR. LINK?

06:47.578 --> 06:49.409
Frankie: LINCOLN McNEIL, AGE 9,
END-STAGE HEART FAILURE,

06:49.409 --> 06:52.623
AWAITING TRANSPLANT,
STATUS 1A.

06:52.623 --> 06:54.745
THERE'S A FAMILY HISTORY
OF THE DISEASE.

06:54.745 --> 06:56.166
THE CAUSE
IS STILL UNKNOWN.

06:56.166 --> 06:59.129
UH, LINK FIRST SHOWED SIGNS
OF CARDIOMYOPATHY TWO WEEKS AGO

06:59.129 --> 07:01.672
AND HAS DETERIORATED
RAPIDLY.

07:01.672 --> 07:03.964
AN ATTEMPT TO PUT HIM
ON A BERLIN HEART FAILED...

07:03.964 --> 07:06.136
DUE TO SOMETHING
I CAN'T REMEMBER.

07:06.136 --> 07:07.347
CLOTTING.

07:07.347 --> 07:08.639
THAT'S IT.

07:08.639 --> 07:12.222
UH, THE PATIENT
IS NOW ON ECMO AND IS...

07:12.222 --> 07:13.013
STABLE.

07:13.013 --> 07:15.015
I COULDN'T HAVE
SAID IT BETTER MYSELF.

07:15.015 --> 07:16.436
THANKS.

07:16.436 --> 07:17.648
SO, WHERE ARE WE
WITH UNOS?

07:17.648 --> 07:20.150
WELL, LINK IS
AT THE TOP OF THE LIST.

07:20.150 --> 07:21.982
HOW MUCH LONGER
CAN HE SURVIVE ON ECMO?

07:21.982 --> 07:25.275
WELL, WITH SWEEP NUMBERS
THIS LOW...

07:25.275 --> 07:27.447
AT LEAST A WEEK.

07:27.447 --> 07:29.069
SO, WE PRAY
FOR A MIRACLE?

07:29.069 --> 07:31.782
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
WE GOT ONE WITH IVY.

07:31.782 --> 07:34.535
WE'RE NOT JUST
SITTING AROUND AND WAITING.

07:34.535 --> 07:37.077
WE ARE AGGRESSIVELY
LOOKING AT OTHER OPTIONS.

07:38.288 --> 07:39.790
IN THE MEANTIME...

07:39.790 --> 07:40.961
[ BAG CRINKLES ]

07:40.961 --> 07:42.633
...HEART-HEALTHY FOOD,
OKAY?

07:44.134 --> 07:47.177
SO, I PUT A CALL IN
TO THESE GUYS FROM STANFORD

07:47.177 --> 07:50.300
WHO ARE DOING ANIMAL TESTING
WITH A DRUG-ELUTING PUMP

07:50.300 --> 07:51.682
TO PREVENT CLOTTING.

07:51.682 --> 07:54.304
NEVER BEEN TRIED ON HUMANS,
BUT LINK IS A LITTLE KID.

07:54.304 --> 07:56.396
THE FIT MIGHT BE RIGHT.
IT COULD WORK.

07:56.396 --> 07:58.358
I'LL LET YOU GUYS KNOW
WHAT THEY SAY.

07:58.358 --> 08:00.601
SO, THAT'S HOW
YOU'RE GONNA PLAY THIS --

08:00.601 --> 08:03.063
ACT LIKE IT'S JUST
ANOTHER DAY AT THE OFFICE?

08:03.063 --> 08:05.065
IT IS.
[ SCOFFS ]

08:05.065 --> 08:06.947
NO, SEE [CHUCKLES]
I NEED DETAILS.

08:06.947 --> 08:08.318
SO,
W-WHAT DID THEY SAY?

08:08.318 --> 08:10.571
"CONGRATULATIONS."
AND THEN
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

08:10.571 --> 08:12.032
"THANK YOU."
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:12.032 --> 08:13.373
CRISTINA,
I JUST DON'T --
NO, NO,
REALLY, REALLY,

08:13.373 --> 08:14.825
IT'S --
IT'S JUST A NOMINATION.

08:14.825 --> 08:18.078
I'M HAPPY ABOUT IT, BUT I'VE GOT
A TON OF WORK TO DO.

08:18.078 --> 08:19.540
I-I WANT TO FOCUS
ON THAT.

08:19.540 --> 08:21.582
I REALLY DON'T WANT
TO MAKE A BIG DEAL OUT OF IT.

08:23.043 --> 08:25.045
HEY, HEY.
UH...LET'S GO THIS WAY.
YEAH.

08:25.045 --> 08:26.506
YOU KNOW,
GET SOME...BREAKFAST?
MM.

08:26.506 --> 08:28.178
WHY?
I GOT MY CHIPS.

08:30.010 --> 08:31.261
All: SURPRISE!

08:31.261 --> 08:33.433
[ ALL CHEERING ]

08:38.979 --> 08:41.852
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:41.852 --> 08:43.063
WHOSE IDEA WAS THIS?

08:43.063 --> 08:44.565
MEREDITH'S.

08:44.565 --> 08:46.196
CONGRATULATIONS.

08:50.030 --> 08:52.653
[ CHEERING CONTINUES ]

09:03.043 --> 09:06.627
INNOVATION. IMAGINATION.
EXCELLENCE.

09:06.627 --> 09:08.338
OH, SOAK IT IN, DOCTORS.

09:08.338 --> 09:10.340
IT'S --
IT'S ALL AROUND YOU.

09:10.340 --> 09:12.512
IT'S MOSTLY
HOVERING AROUND DR. YANG,

09:12.512 --> 09:14.595
AND SHANE'S
KIND OF HOGGING HER.

09:14.595 --> 09:16.386
I'M NOT JUST
TALKING ABOUT DR. YANG.

09:16.386 --> 09:18.268
DR. SHEPHERD IS TESTING
A NEW MACHINE

09:18.268 --> 09:20.480
THAT CAN READ EMOTIONS
AND HAS APPLICATIONS

09:20.480 --> 09:22.562
FOR THE WORK THAT
HE AND DR. TORRES ARE DOING.

09:22.562 --> 09:24.064
[ GASPS ]
TORRES! ME!

09:24.064 --> 09:26.356
HEY, DR. GREY
IS ABOUT TO DO THE FIRST

09:26.356 --> 09:29.860
HIV-POSITIVE-TO-POSITIVE
KIDNEY TRANSPLANT IN THE STATE

09:29.860 --> 09:31.902
SINCE THE NEW LAW
WENT INTO EFFECT IN NOVEMBER.

09:31.902 --> 09:33.323
THAT'S HISTORY IN THE MAKING.
IT'S MINE.

09:33.323 --> 09:34.825
A-AND DR. BAILEY'S
LOOKING FOR

09:34.825 --> 09:37.157
A GENETIC CURE FOR A KID
WHO LACKS AN IMMUNE SYSTEM.

09:38.368 --> 09:39.499
EDWARDS?

09:39.499 --> 09:41.371
I WAS ON HER SERVICE YESTERDAY.
SHE'S NOT DOING ANYTHING.

09:41.371 --> 09:43.203
SHE'S JUST STARING
AT HER COMPUTER SCREEN.

09:43.203 --> 09:45.335
THAT IS NOT NOTHING.
SHE'S THINKING.

09:45.335 --> 09:46.707
H-HER BRAIN IS TURNING,

09:46.707 --> 09:49.299
BUILDING UP TO THAT MOMENT
OF -- OF INSPIRATION.

09:49.299 --> 09:51.421
IT'LL LOOK LIKE NOTHING,
BUT IN A MOMENT,

09:51.421 --> 09:54.304
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]
POW! 4th OF JULY.

09:54.304 --> 09:56.136
DON'T BLINK.
YOU'LL MISS IT.

09:57.557 --> 09:59.680
IT WAS LIKE THAT
WITH ME AND YANG AT FIRST, TOO.

09:59.680 --> 10:01.772
[ SIGHS ] A LOT OF STARING
AT COMPUTER SCREENS,

10:01.772 --> 10:03.223
AND NOW LOOK AT US.

10:03.223 --> 10:05.185
OH, SHANE.

10:06.897 --> 10:08.649
OH, SHANE, SHANE, SHANE.

10:08.649 --> 10:09.569
NO.

10:09.569 --> 10:11.902
I WASN'T GONNA DO THIS
TO YOU TODAY.

10:11.902 --> 10:13.403
I REALLY WASN'T.
WAS I, LADIES?

10:13.403 --> 10:14.534
SHE WASN'T.
HAND TO GOD.

10:14.534 --> 10:15.906
BUT YOU JUST GOT TOO BIG
FOR YOUR BRITCHES.

10:15.906 --> 10:17.237
IT'S NOT EVEN
INTERESTING STUFF.

10:17.237 --> 10:19.159
I'M JUST IN THE PRINTING LAB
MAKING SAMPLE CONDUITS.

10:19.159 --> 10:22.082
WELL, NOT ANYMORE,
SWAP MONKEY!

10:22.082 --> 10:24.124
ENJOY WORKING WITH
DR. BAILEY.

10:24.124 --> 10:26.006
POW! 4th OF JULY!

10:26.006 --> 10:27.337
[ LAUGHTER ]

10:27.337 --> 10:28.298
SUCKS.

10:28.298 --> 10:29.169
SWAP MONKEY!

10:29.169 --> 10:30.420
OKAY, GUYS,
BEAR WITH ME.

10:30.420 --> 10:32.212
I KNOW WE'VE GONE THROUGH
ALL THIS BEFORE,

10:32.212 --> 10:34.554
BUT THE HOSPITAL JUST NEEDS
YOUR CONSENT ONE MORE TIME.

10:34.554 --> 10:36.216
GO AHEAD, MURPHY.
STATE YOUR NAME.

10:36.216 --> 10:37.517
KEITH KALBER.

10:37.517 --> 10:39.720
KEITH, YOU UNDERSTAND THAT
THE KIDNEY YOU'RE GETTING TODAY

10:39.720 --> 10:42.352
IS BEING DONATED FROM A PERSON
INFECTED WITH HIV?

10:42.352 --> 10:44.144
I SHOULD HOPE SO.

10:44.144 --> 10:46.186
I WAS THERE
THE DAY HE GOT HIS DIAGNOSIS.

10:46.186 --> 10:49.189
AND ALTHOUGH SMALL, THERE IS
A RISK OF SUPERINFECTION

10:49.189 --> 10:51.531
BY MIXING HIS STRAIN
OF THE VIRUS WITH YOURS.

10:51.531 --> 10:53.613
KNOWING THIS,
DO YOU STILL WISH TO PROCEED?

10:53.613 --> 10:55.275
I DO.

10:55.275 --> 10:57.617
GOD, IT FEELS LIKE
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED.

10:57.617 --> 10:59.539
HOW WOULD YOU KNOW
HOW THAT FEELS?

10:59.539 --> 11:00.701
[ Chuckling ]
EXCUSE ME?

11:00.701 --> 11:02.282
HE ALWAYS HAS
THE BEST BOYFRIENDS,

11:02.282 --> 11:03.874
BUT HE REFUSES
TO COMMIT.

11:03.874 --> 11:07.247
CAN WE JUST GET BACK TO
MY HUGE SACRIFICE?

11:07.247 --> 11:08.378
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:08.378 --> 11:09.880
MARTY [CHUCKLES]
YOU UNDERSTAND

11:09.880 --> 11:12.092
THAT THE RISKS OF DONATION
ARE SIMILAR TO THOSE INVOLVED

11:12.092 --> 11:15.215
WITH ANY MAJOR SURGERY,
SUCH AS BLEEDING AND INFECTION?

11:15.215 --> 11:17.257
AND DEATH RESULTING
FROM KIDNEY DONATION

11:17.257 --> 11:19.599
IS EXTREMELY RARE.

11:19.599 --> 11:21.511
DEFINE..."EXTREMELY."

11:21.511 --> 11:24.264
UH, .06%.

11:25.896 --> 11:28.228
OH.
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

11:30.070 --> 11:32.192
WE'VE BEATEN WORSE ODDS.

11:32.192 --> 11:33.443
OH, YEAH.

11:33.443 --> 11:35.275
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:38.949 --> 11:40.700
NOW, BEFORE WE DRILL
INTO SOMEONE'S BRAIN,

11:40.700 --> 11:43.323
WE NEED TO MAKE SURE
THEY'RE GOOD CANDIDATES
FOR ROBOTICS WORK.

11:43.323 --> 11:44.995
THEY NEED TO BE
MOTIVATED, STABLE,

11:44.995 --> 11:46.286
AND NEUROLOGICALLY HEALTHY.

11:46.286 --> 11:48.088
THIS MACHINE GIVES US
A WINDOW INTO ALL THAT.

11:48.088 --> 11:49.539
MM-HMM. YEAH,
YOU'RE GONNA BE OUR BASELINE.

11:49.539 --> 11:51.251
SO, WE'RE JUST GONNA SHOW YOU
SOME PICTURES,

11:51.251 --> 11:52.542
AND ALL YOU NEED TO DO
IS LOOK AT THEM.

11:52.542 --> 11:54.004
[ CLICK ]

11:59.679 --> 12:00.801
DEREK: Okay, Wilson,
you ready?

12:00.801 --> 12:03.303
[ MACHINE WHIRS,
COMPUTER BEEPS ]

12:04.724 --> 12:06.686
Callie: MM.
THAT'S THE AMYGDALA, RIGHT?

12:06.686 --> 12:08.809
IT'S FIRED UP
BY POWERFUL NEGATIVE EMOTIONS,

12:08.809 --> 12:10.190
LIKE FEAR, RAGE,
ANGER, HATE.

12:10.190 --> 12:11.691
OKAY,
NOW LET'S TAKE A LOOK

12:11.691 --> 12:14.274
[ SCRIBBLING ]
AT HER NUCLEUS ACCUMBENS.

12:14.274 --> 12:15.655
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]
HER PLEASURE CENTER?

12:15.655 --> 12:17.317
MM-HMM.
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

12:18.738 --> 12:19.990
[ COMPUTER BUZZES ]
HMM.

12:19.990 --> 12:21.782
THAT'S NOT
SUPPOSED TO HAPPEN.

12:21.782 --> 12:24.284
WILSON, WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?
YOU DON'T LIKE CATS?

12:24.284 --> 12:25.285
HATE 'EM.

12:28.038 --> 12:29.169
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

12:29.169 --> 12:30.330
[ COMPUTER BUZZES ]

12:30.330 --> 12:32.082
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THE BEACH?

12:32.082 --> 12:33.633
Sand in my eyes,
skin cancer,

12:33.633 --> 12:35.876
vacations I never got to take
as a child.

12:35.876 --> 12:38.338
UH-OH. OPEN, COMMINUTED
RADIUS FRACTURE IN THE E.R.

12:38.338 --> 12:40.340
[ COMPUTER DINGING ]
THERE WE GO.
LOOK AT THAT.

12:40.340 --> 12:42.012
TOOK A BROKEN ARM
TO MAKE HER HAPPY.

12:42.012 --> 12:43.223
HUH.

12:43.223 --> 12:45.225
I TURNED HER ON TO ORTHO
A FEW WEEKS AGO. WATCH THIS.

12:45.225 --> 12:47.307
HEY, WILSON, YOU WANT TO GO
SET THAT ARM YOURSELF?

12:47.307 --> 12:49.149
[ COMPUTER DINGS RAPIDLY ]

12:49.149 --> 12:50.480
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LOVE OUR NEW TOY.

12:58.108 --> 12:59.659
YANG GET TOO FANCY
FOR YOU,

12:59.659 --> 13:01.781
KICKED YOU DOWN HERE
TO THE "B" TEAM?

13:01.781 --> 13:06.116
OH, NO. I, UH [SIGHS] WANTED
TO SEE THE WORK YOU'RE DOING.

13:06.116 --> 13:09.329
GENOME SEQUENCING IS
THE FUTURE OF MEDICINE.

13:09.329 --> 13:12.252
MAY NOT BE A FANCY SURGERY,
BUT IT'S GONNA SAVE LIVES.

13:12.252 --> 13:14.714
YOU WANT TO SAVE LIVES
OR GO TO FANCY AWARD DINNERS?

13:14.714 --> 13:16.126
SAVE LIVES.

13:16.126 --> 13:17.547
DON'T GET ME WRONG.

13:17.547 --> 13:20.420
I'M HAPPY FOR DR. YANG.
WHY WOULDN'T I BE?

13:20.420 --> 13:23.223
I TRAINED HER,
MOLDED HER.

13:23.223 --> 13:25.305
IT'S ALMOST LIKE
IT'S MY NOMINATION, TOO.

13:25.305 --> 13:27.307
KEITH AND MARTY
ARE GOOD TO GO.

13:27.307 --> 13:29.890
AH, YES -- YOUR HIGH-PROFILE
KIDNEY TRANSPLANT.

13:29.890 --> 13:31.852
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
HARVESTING THE DONOR.

13:31.852 --> 13:33.563
YEAH, WHILE YOU DO
THE AWARD-WINNING STUFF.

13:33.563 --> 13:35.355
UH, YEAH, I REMEMBER.

13:35.355 --> 13:37.067
PAGE ME
WHEN YOU'RE READY.

13:38.778 --> 13:40.360
TRAINED HER, TOO.

13:40.360 --> 13:42.362
Cristina: THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR GETTING BACK TO ME.

13:42.362 --> 13:46.286
I HEAR YOU'RE DEVELOPING,
UH, A DRUG-ELUTING CARDIAC PUMP

13:46.286 --> 13:49.369
THAT'S GETTING EXCELLENT RESULTS
IN SHEEP.

13:49.369 --> 13:51.161
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]
YES, THAT'S ME.

13:51.161 --> 13:53.213
UH, WELL, THERE ARE
FOUR OTHER EXCELLENT SURGEONS

13:53.213 --> 13:54.374
WHO ARE NOMINATED.

13:54.374 --> 13:55.455
THANK YOU.

13:55.455 --> 13:56.836
UM...

13:56.836 --> 13:59.219
UH, YES.
ANYWAY, I HAVE A YOUNG PATIENT.

13:59.219 --> 14:01.261
HE'S ON DAY 10 OF ECMO

14:01.261 --> 14:04.174
AND HAS, UH,
PROTEIN "S" DEFICIENCY.

14:05.265 --> 14:07.888
SORRY?

14:07.888 --> 14:11.471
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
I'M 3-D PRINTING, UH,
CONDUITS FOR HLHS PATIENTS.

14:11.471 --> 14:13.063
UH-HUH. YEAH.

14:13.063 --> 14:15.976
UH, WELL, I THINK MY PATIENT
WOULD BE AN EXCELLENT CANDIDATE

14:15.976 --> 14:17.938
FOR A COMPASSIONATE
RELEASE.

14:17.938 --> 14:19.109
Woman: IN HERE.

14:19.109 --> 14:20.150
I-I SEE.

14:20.150 --> 14:22.572
OH, GOD.
OH, NO, NO, NO. WHAT?

14:22.572 --> 14:24.244
THE LITTLE BOY'S ECMO CIRCUIT
CLOTTED OFF,

14:24.244 --> 14:25.825
AND HE'S NOT RESPONDING
TO FLUIDS.

14:25.825 --> 14:28.748
UM, PAGE DR. HUNT
AND, UM, DR. ROBBINS.

14:28.748 --> 14:30.250
OKAY, LET'S GET HIM
OFF THAT BED...

14:30.250 --> 14:31.161
MAN: Dr. Yang?

14:31.161 --> 14:34.414
Dr, Yang,
is everything all right?

14:34.414 --> 14:36.206
Dr, Yang? Hello?

14:38.258 --> 14:39.759
[ Voice breaking ]
SHE CAN'T TALK RIGHT NOW.

14:51.811 --> 14:53.013
HE'S CLOTTING,
EVEN ON THE HEPARIN.

14:53.013 --> 14:54.684
I CAN'T GIVE HIM ANY MORE
OR HE'LL BLEED OUT,

14:54.684 --> 14:57.067
AND I CAN'T GIVE HIM ANY LESS
OR HE'LL KEEP CLOTTING.

14:57.067 --> 14:59.609
WE NEED THE STANFORD
ARTIFICIAL HEART.

14:59.609 --> 15:01.021
WE CAN'T HAVE IT.

15:01.021 --> 15:01.942
WHAT?

15:01.942 --> 15:04.694
IT'S NOT THEM.
THEY WANT TO LET US TRY.

15:04.694 --> 15:06.196
IT'S THE FDA.

15:06.196 --> 15:07.787
THEY'RE BEING
CONSERVATIVE

15:07.787 --> 15:09.950
AND INSISTING
ON ONE MORE ANIMAL TRIAL.

15:09.950 --> 15:12.032
THEY'RE SIX MONTHS AWAY
FROM APPROVAL.

15:12.032 --> 15:13.203
Arizona:
OKAY, SO WHAT DO WE DO?

15:13.203 --> 15:15.535
WE HOPE UNOS CALLS.

15:15.535 --> 15:18.088
[ SIGHS ] TODAY.

15:18.088 --> 15:19.089
YEAH.

15:28.758 --> 15:32.973
OKAY, TIME TO GET YOU
PREPPED AND READY FOR --

15:34.264 --> 15:36.896
I CAN'T DO IT.

15:36.896 --> 15:38.018
UH, KEITH'S RIGHT.

15:38.018 --> 15:41.731
I MEAN,
W-W-W-WE'VE BEATEN HUGE ODDS.

15:41.731 --> 15:46.196
I MEAN, WE'RE STILL ALIVE WHILE
SO MANY OF OUR FRIENDS DIED.

15:46.196 --> 15:50.070
AND I'VE BEEN HEALTHY
FOR SO LONG NOW.

15:50.070 --> 15:52.702
Y-- [EXHALES]
YOU GET A LITTLE COCKY.

15:52.702 --> 15:55.375
YOU FORGET
HOW LUCKY YOU ARE.

15:55.375 --> 15:57.077
AND I...

15:57.077 --> 16:00.540
I-I'M THE MOST HORRIBLE FRIEND,
BUT I JUST...

16:00.540 --> 16:01.791
I'M SCARED.

16:01.791 --> 16:07.347
W-WHAT IF
I'M ONE OF THE .06%?

16:07.347 --> 16:12.012
I-I-I DON'T THINK I CAN GIVE HIM
[CLEARS THROAT] MY KIDNEY.

16:12.012 --> 16:14.054
HAVE YOU TOLD KEITH?

16:14.054 --> 16:15.395
[ SIGHS ]

16:15.395 --> 16:18.018
H-H-HE'S BEEN SUFFERING
FOR SO LONG,

16:18.018 --> 16:21.061
A-AND WHEN THE LAW WAS PASSED,
HE WAS SO HAPPY.

16:21.061 --> 16:24.194
AND THEN I TURNED OUT
TO BE A PERFECT MATCH.

16:24.194 --> 16:26.276
A-AND NOW...

16:26.276 --> 16:29.449
HOW CAN I LOOK MY BEST FRIEND
IN THE EYE

16:29.449 --> 16:32.162
AND TELL HIM
I WON'T SAVE HIS LIFE?

16:37.457 --> 16:40.920
IT IS UNFORTUNATE,
BUT...IT DOES HAPPEN.

16:40.920 --> 16:43.793
WE MISREAD THE SCREENING,
AND IT TURNS OUT

16:43.793 --> 16:46.926
THAT MARTY IS NOT
A SUITABLE DONOR.

16:47.967 --> 16:50.510
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

16:50.510 --> 16:52.972
YEAH, UH,
THIS IS OUTRAGEOUS.

16:52.972 --> 16:55.014
I'M -- I-I'M --
I'M COMPLETELY SHOCKED.

16:55.014 --> 16:56.346
SO WERE WE.

16:56.346 --> 16:58.228
SHOCKED AND DISAPPOINTED.

16:58.228 --> 17:00.019
Keith: SO, WHAT NOW?

17:00.019 --> 17:02.902
Meredith: WELL,
YOU'LL CONTINUE ON DIALYSIS

17:02.902 --> 17:05.065
AND GO BACK
ON THE TRANSPLANT LIST.

17:05.065 --> 17:06.196
[ SIGHS ]

17:06.196 --> 17:07.277
[ SCOFFS ]

17:07.277 --> 17:10.240
YOU KNOW,
IT'S IRONIC.

17:10.240 --> 17:13.032
I SPEND YEARS
FIGHTING HIV.

17:13.032 --> 17:14.954
I GET MYSELF
TO THE POINT

17:14.954 --> 17:17.917
WHERE THE VIRUS IS VIRTUALLY
NONEXISTENT IN MY BODY.

17:17.917 --> 17:19.119
[ SIGHS ]

17:19.119 --> 17:20.870
I SURVIVE.

17:20.870 --> 17:24.043
AND NOW I DIE
OF KIDNEY DISEASE.

17:24.043 --> 17:25.044
I'M SO SORRY.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.966
[ Sobbing ]
I'M SO, SO SORRY.

17:26.966 --> 17:29.929
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.
YOU TRIED.

17:29.929 --> 17:32.051
YOU -- YOU --
YOU STEPPED UP.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.433
OH, GOD.

17:33.433 --> 17:36.015
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WOULD DO
WITHOUT YOU.

17:40.270 --> 17:41.271
[ INTERCOM CLICKS ]

17:41.271 --> 17:42.942
Derek: WHAT DO YOU DO
FOR A LIVING?

17:42.942 --> 17:44.444
I'm an orthopedic surgeon.

17:44.444 --> 17:46.856
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

17:46.856 --> 17:47.897
DO YOU ENJOY YOUR WORK?

17:47.897 --> 17:49.279
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LOVE IT.

17:49.279 --> 17:50.490
Are you married?
YEP.

17:50.490 --> 17:51.571
Any kids?

17:51.571 --> 17:52.952
UH, ONE.

17:52.952 --> 17:54.954
Would you consider yourself
a happy person?

17:54.954 --> 17:56.116
EXTREMELY.

17:56.116 --> 17:58.118
And you want to participate
in this project?

17:58.118 --> 17:59.199
I DO.

17:59.199 --> 18:00.750
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

18:00.750 --> 18:02.122
No.

18:02.122 --> 18:03.543
"NO" WHAT?

18:03.543 --> 18:07.086
Uh, judging by these results,
I'd say you are depressed,

18:07.086 --> 18:09.008
and I would turn you away
from the study.

18:09.008 --> 18:10.420
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'M NOT DEPRESSED.

18:10.420 --> 18:12.762
Oh, it's no big deal.
We can get somebody else
to give us a baseline --

18:12.762 --> 18:14.804
Derek, I'm not depressed.
Show me the kitten.

18:14.804 --> 18:16.846
[ KEYBOARD CLACKS,
COMPUTER BEEPS ]

18:16.846 --> 18:18.978
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:18.978 --> 18:20.019
YEAH. SEE?

18:20.019 --> 18:22.222
I'M HAPPY.

18:22.222 --> 18:23.983
[ COMPUTER BUZZES ]
Am I happy?

18:23.983 --> 18:25.145
Nope.

18:25.145 --> 18:26.226
WELL...

18:27.647 --> 18:28.858
OKAY, WELL, UH --

18:28.858 --> 18:30.029
NO! WHY ARE YOU --

18:30.029 --> 18:31.691
[ SIGHS ]

18:31.691 --> 18:33.233
I -- I REALLY DO
LOVE KITTENS.

18:33.233 --> 18:34.404
I DO.

18:34.404 --> 18:36.286
HEY, DR. TORRES SAID
YOU HAVE A THING FOR BONES.

18:36.286 --> 18:37.827
WHEN YOU'RE DONE
WITH HER PATIENT,

18:37.827 --> 18:39.869
YOU WANT TO DO
A MANDIBULAR O.R.I.F.?

18:39.869 --> 18:41.501
YES!

18:41.501 --> 18:43.333
I SEE YOU HAVE
ANOTHER BEVERAGE.

18:43.333 --> 18:45.004
ICED TEA, ACTUALLY.
IT'S QUITE GOOD.

18:45.004 --> 18:45.915
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME?

18:45.915 --> 18:48.168
OH, I'M PERFECTLY HAPPY
WITH MY WATER.

18:48.168 --> 18:50.840
IS THAT A --
HER SWIMSUIT.
YEAH. RACERBACK.

18:50.840 --> 18:51.961
I RAN OUT OF UNDERWEAR.

18:51.961 --> 18:53.843
I'M NOT UNDERSTANDING.

18:53.843 --> 18:55.515
YOU DON'T WEAR SWIMSUITS WHEN
YOU RUN OUT OF CLEAN UNDERWEAR?

18:55.515 --> 18:56.886
I DON'T RUN OUT
OF CLEAN UNDERWEAR.

18:56.886 --> 18:58.718
YOU'RE A RESIDENT.
WHEN DO YOU HAVE
TIME TO DO LAUNDRY?

18:58.718 --> 18:59.889
I'M A DOCTOR.
I SEND IT OUT.

18:59.889 --> 19:01.060
HMM.

19:03.893 --> 19:06.396
THE INCISION LOOKS GOOD.

19:06.396 --> 19:07.687
WHERE ARE MY PARENTS?

19:07.687 --> 19:09.939
THEY WENT TO CHECK OUT
A SUPPORT GROUP WE HAVE

19:09.939 --> 19:11.321
FOR DEALING
WITH TOUGH STUFF.

19:11.321 --> 19:12.862
I'M THE ONE
WHO'S STUCK IN HERE.

19:12.862 --> 19:14.654
YOU WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT?

19:14.654 --> 19:15.445
NO.

19:15.445 --> 19:17.617
WANT TO PLAY CHECKERS?

19:17.617 --> 19:18.408
NO.

19:18.408 --> 19:19.949
CHESS?

19:19.949 --> 19:21.040
NO.

19:21.040 --> 19:23.493
COME ON. YOU GOT TO LET ME
BEAT YOU AT SOMETHING.

19:23.493 --> 19:25.745
I KIND OF FEEL LIKE PLAYING
WITH SOMEONE MY OWN AGE.

19:25.745 --> 19:27.166
[ CAR THUDS ]

19:27.166 --> 19:28.788
WHOA! WHOA!
CAREFUL.

19:28.788 --> 19:30.880
YOU'RE GONNA RIP
THROUGH THE PLASTIC.

19:30.880 --> 19:32.131
[ CAR WHIRRING ]

19:32.131 --> 19:33.923
THAT'S THE POINT.

19:37.467 --> 19:43.763
♪ SISTER CHRISTIAN,
OH, THE TIME HAS COME ♪

19:43.763 --> 19:47.857
♪ AND YOU KNOW THAT YOU'RE
THE ONLY ONE TO SAY ♪

19:47.857 --> 19:49.269
SURGERY'S OFF.

19:49.269 --> 19:51.070
IT'S OFF?

19:51.070 --> 19:53.022
DONOR BACKED OUT.
[ SIGHS ]

19:53.022 --> 19:56.075
PLEASE TELL CRISTINA
I'M THRILLED FOR HER.

19:56.075 --> 19:58.368
I'M SURE SHE'D LOVE
TO HEAR IT FROM YOU.

19:58.368 --> 20:00.410
AND I WOULD LOVE
TO HAVE THAT CONVERSATION,

20:00.410 --> 20:02.532
BUT I AM BUSY
TRYING TO FIND A WAY

20:02.532 --> 20:05.625
FOR A GENE TO PROLIFERATE
IN THE BODY OF A YOUNG BOY.

20:05.625 --> 20:09.168
SO I WOULD BE MOST GRATEFUL
IF YOU WOULD EXTEND

20:09.168 --> 20:12.882
MY HEARTFELT CONGRATULATIONS
TO DR. YANG FOR ME.

20:12.882 --> 20:16.045
♪ MOTORIN' ♪

20:16.045 --> 20:18.298
UM...OKAY.

20:21.551 --> 20:22.722
[ DOOR OPENS ]

20:22.722 --> 20:27.557
♪ IN FINDING MR. RIGHT ♪

20:27.557 --> 20:28.768
YOU SAID
HE WAS STABLE.

20:28.768 --> 20:30.650
YOU SAID HE HAD AT LEAST
ONE MORE WEEK ON ECMO.

20:30.650 --> 20:32.352
W-WE THOUGHT THAT WE HAD IT
UNDER CONTROL,

20:32.352 --> 20:33.853
AND WE DIDN'T EXPECT
FOR HIM TO CLOT.

20:33.853 --> 20:36.526
AND SIX MONTHS AGO,
I DIDN'T EXPECT ANY OF THIS.

20:36.526 --> 20:38.818
I WAS IN A CARPOOL LINE
PICKING UP

20:38.818 --> 20:42.992
[ Voice breaking ] MY THREE
HAPPY, HEALTHY KIDS FROM SCHOOL.

20:42.992 --> 20:44.744
AND NOW --
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:44.744 --> 20:47.827
NOW I HAVE TWO KIDS
IN END-STAGE HEART FAILURE

20:47.827 --> 20:51.000
AND ONE -- ONE BEING KEPT ALIVE
WITH A PACEMAKER.

20:51.000 --> 20:53.373
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU GUYS CAN'T TELL ME
WHY MY KIDS ARE SICK,

20:53.373 --> 20:55.505
AND -- AND NOW
YOU'RE SCRATCHING YOUR HEADS,

20:55.505 --> 20:58.338
TELLING ME THAT THERE'S
NOTHING MORE YOU CAN DO FOR LINK

20:58.338 --> 21:01.010
EXCEPT -- EXCEPT WAIT?

21:01.010 --> 21:03.883
I THOUGHT YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO
BE SOME AWARD-WINNING DOCTOR.
Owen: FRANKIE.

21:03.883 --> 21:05.805
MY PARENTS KEEP SAYING
YOU'RE DOING YOUR BEST,

21:05.805 --> 21:07.687
BUT YOUR BEST IS BAD.

21:08.598 --> 21:10.940
Sabine: FRANKIE, WAIT!

21:10.940 --> 21:12.061
FRANKIE!

21:12.061 --> 21:16.896
♪ IN FINDING MR. RIGHT ♪

21:16.896 --> 21:21.070
♪ YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT TONIGHT ♪

21:27.617 --> 21:28.958
[ SLURPS ]

21:28.958 --> 21:29.959
Man: DR. YANG?

21:29.959 --> 21:32.041
I'M A...INTERN HERE.

21:32.041 --> 21:33.463
I JUST WANT TO SAY
CONGRATULATIONS.

21:33.463 --> 21:34.714
YOU ARE TOTALLY
GONNA WIN.

21:34.714 --> 21:36.916
ARE YOU FROM THE FUTURE?
[ CHUCKLES ] NO.

21:36.916 --> 21:38.628
THEN SHUT UP.

21:38.628 --> 21:39.879
SHE MEANS "THANK YOU."

21:39.879 --> 21:41.050
[ SLURPS ]

21:41.050 --> 21:42.051
[ SIGHS ]

21:44.424 --> 21:45.885
ANYBODY WANT
SOME MEATLOAF?

21:45.885 --> 21:47.807
MNH-MNH.

21:47.807 --> 21:49.849
ISN'T THAT THE MEATLOAF
YOU HAD YESTERDAY?

21:49.849 --> 21:51.230
YEP. AND THE DAY
BEFORE THAT.

21:51.230 --> 21:52.892
PROBABLY GONNA HAVE IT
TOMORROW, TOO,

21:52.892 --> 21:54.564
'CAUSE THERE'S STILL A PIECE
LEFT AT HOME.

21:54.564 --> 21:56.566
JACKSON DOESN'T
EAT LEFTOVERS, YOU SEE.

21:56.566 --> 21:58.107
HE SAYS
HE FINDS IT DEPRESSING

21:58.107 --> 22:00.239
TO EAT FOOD OUT OF
A TUPPERWARE CONTAINER.

22:00.239 --> 22:02.862
YOU KNOW WHAT I FIND DEPRESSING?
PAYING $7 FOR A HAMBURGER.

22:02.862 --> 22:03.903
MAKE HER STOP.

22:03.903 --> 22:04.904
[ CALLIE SLURPING ]

22:04.904 --> 22:06.906
HER, TOO.

22:06.906 --> 22:08.868
HEY.
[ SLAMS CUP ] AH.

22:08.868 --> 22:09.909
OH.

22:09.909 --> 22:11.000
IT WAS LOW BLOOD SUGAR,
SHEPHERD.

22:11.000 --> 22:12.792
TAKE THAT FOOD TO GO.
WE'RE GONNA DO THIS AGAIN.

22:12.792 --> 22:13.913
COME ON! COME ON!
LET'S GO!

22:13.913 --> 22:16.045
HMM.

22:16.045 --> 22:18.418
THERE SHE IS.

22:18.418 --> 22:20.259
THE FUTURE OF MEDICINE.

22:20.259 --> 22:21.340
HOW'S IT FEEL?

22:21.340 --> 22:23.723
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

22:23.723 --> 22:25.344
O-KAY.

22:25.344 --> 22:26.926
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

22:26.926 --> 22:29.469
YOUR MOTHER
WAS THE SAME WAY.

22:30.560 --> 22:32.812
DIDN'T YOU HAVE
THAT MEATLOAF YESTERDAY?

22:32.812 --> 22:33.813
MM-HMM.
MM-HMM. YEP.

22:33.813 --> 22:34.974
AND THE DAY
BEFORE THAT.

22:34.974 --> 22:36.476
AND PROBABLY
GONNA HAVE IT TOMORROW.

22:36.476 --> 22:37.567
DR. GREY?

22:37.567 --> 22:39.028
YOU'RE GONNA KILL ME.

22:41.821 --> 22:43.823
I'M GONNA THANK
MY PARENTS, OBVIOUSLY.

22:43.823 --> 22:46.115
WHY? THEY DIDN'T HELP YOU
WIN THE HARPER AVERY.

22:46.115 --> 22:47.947
THEY GAVE BIRTH TO ME.

22:47.947 --> 22:49.989
THEY SHOULD BE
PUBLICLY ACKNOWLEDGED.

22:49.989 --> 22:51.330
I DON'T HAVE PARENTS,

22:51.330 --> 22:53.623
SO I'M NOT GONNA WASTE
ANY OF MY SPEECH ON THEM.

22:53.623 --> 22:56.416
IT'S GONNA BE ALL ABOUT ME.
HUMBLE BUT...

22:56.416 --> 22:57.457
SELF-INVOLVED.

22:57.457 --> 22:58.998
EXACTLY.

22:58.998 --> 23:00.840
CAN YOU STOP?
WHAT'S WRONG, SHANE?

23:00.840 --> 23:03.262
[ Chuckling ]
SWAP MONKEY MISSES HIS CONDUITS?

23:03.262 --> 23:05.174
PLEASE -- SWAP BACK.

23:05.174 --> 23:06.596
BAILEY SAYS
SHE'S ON THE VERGE.

23:06.596 --> 23:09.429
Stephanie: NO, BAILEY'S BEEN
ON THE VERGE FOR DAYS.

23:09.429 --> 23:10.510
I'M KEEPING YANG.

23:10.510 --> 23:11.511
WHERE IS IT?!

23:11.511 --> 23:12.812
WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR?

23:12.812 --> 23:14.604
I'M LOOKING FOR A PICTURE
OF THE HARPER AVERY.

23:14.604 --> 23:15.935
OOH!

23:15.935 --> 23:17.016
IT'S MY SCREEN SAVER.

23:17.016 --> 23:19.569
I KNOW WHAT THE HARPER AVERY
LOOKS LIKE.

23:19.569 --> 23:21.150
I'M LOOKING FOR A PICTURE
OF ELLIS GREY'S HARPER AVERY.

23:21.150 --> 23:22.191
WHY?

23:22.191 --> 23:23.483
I REMEMBER
BEING IN MEDICAL SCHOOL

23:23.483 --> 23:24.734
AND LOOKING
AT THESE OLD MEDICAL JOURNALS

23:24.734 --> 23:26.826
AND SEEING A PICTURE OF HER
FROM THE FIRST TIME SHE WON.

23:26.826 --> 23:28.948
SHE WAS YOUNG.
SHE WAS LIKE 35 OR SOMETHING.

23:28.948 --> 23:29.869
I'M ALMOST 35.

23:29.869 --> 23:31.160
YOU'RE 27.

23:31.160 --> 23:33.453
MY LIFE IS STUPID
AND ORDINARY.

23:33.453 --> 23:35.535
AND...I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT I'M DOING HERE.

23:35.535 --> 23:36.996
I'M NEVER GONNA WIN
A HARPER AVERY.

23:36.996 --> 23:39.418
I MIGHT AS WELL JUST MOVE
TO A FARM AND GROW VEGETABLES.

23:39.418 --> 23:40.800
AT LEAST I'D BE DOING
SOMETHING USEFUL.

23:40.800 --> 23:42.542
HER TRANSPLANT
GOT CANCELED.

23:42.542 --> 23:44.714
YOU WANT
TO BE ON BAILEY?
[ PAGER BEEPS ]

23:44.714 --> 23:46.305
OH, MY GOD.
OH, MY GOD!

23:47.306 --> 23:48.097
OH, MY GOD!

23:50.309 --> 23:52.311
OOH! FRIES! YEAH!

23:52.311 --> 23:54.313
THE SURGERY IS BACK ON?

23:54.313 --> 23:55.515
WELL, KIND OF.

23:55.515 --> 23:57.316
MARTY FELT TERRIBLE,
SO HE'S BACK ON BOARD.

23:57.316 --> 23:59.318
BUT WE TOLD KEITH
THAT THEY WEREN'T A GOOD MATCH.

23:59.318 --> 24:00.730
YOU DID WHAT?

24:00.730 --> 24:02.772
THEY'RE BEST FRIENDS,
AND I WAS TRYING TO HELP!

24:02.772 --> 24:05.525
YOU GOT EMOTIONALLY INVOLVED.
ROOKIE MISTAKE.

24:05.525 --> 24:07.827
I AM NOT A ROOKIE.

24:07.827 --> 24:09.949
BUT I DON'T KNOW HOW I'M GONNA
GO BACK AND EXPLAIN THIS.

24:09.949 --> 24:11.661
OH, I DO.

24:13.913 --> 24:16.335
DR. GREY
MISREAD THE LABS.

24:16.335 --> 24:19.378
HER RELATIVE INEXPERIENCE
LED TO A TERRIBLE ERROR.

24:19.378 --> 24:22.381
YOU TWO ARE, IN FACT,
A PERFECT MATCH.

24:22.381 --> 24:23.462
WOW!
WOW.

24:23.462 --> 24:25.795
I MEAN,
THIS IS SUCH GREAT NEWS.

24:25.795 --> 24:27.797
SO SORRY,
KEITH.

24:27.797 --> 24:30.930
I'M WILLING TO JUST PUT ALL THIS
BEHIND ME AND MOVE FORWARD.

24:30.930 --> 24:33.142
WELL, YOU KNOW
HOW THESE YOUNG SURGEONS ARE.

24:33.142 --> 24:37.186
IT'S ALL ABOUT P.R. AND AWARDS,
AND THEY GET SLOPPY.

24:37.186 --> 24:39.809
HE SAID HE'S READY
TO MOVE FORWARD.

24:39.809 --> 24:42.812
LUCKILY, I'M AVAILABLE
TO DO YOUR TRANSPLANT,

24:42.812 --> 24:46.065
AND I ASSURE YOU [CHUCKLES]
I AM SUBSTANCE OVER FLASH.

24:46.065 --> 24:48.778
I THOUGHT YOU WERE DOING
MARTY'S SURGERY.

24:48.778 --> 24:51.030
WELL, I-I-I DON'T MIND
TAKING DR. GREY.

24:51.030 --> 24:53.072
WELL,
WHY SHOULD YOU SETTLE?

24:53.072 --> 24:55.785
WELL, SHE'S, YOU KNOW,
JUST TAKING OUT MY KIDNEY.

24:55.785 --> 24:56.956
HOW HARD COULD IT BE,
YOU KNOW?

24:56.956 --> 24:58.077
BUT SHE CAN BARELY READ
A LAB REPORT.

24:58.077 --> 24:59.619
YOU DON'T KNOW
IF SHE'S GONNA

24:59.619 --> 25:01.581
MISTAKE YOUR GALLBLADDER
FOR YOUR KIDNEY.

25:01.581 --> 25:04.924
GUYS, I ASSURE YOU --
I'M AN EXCELLENT SURGEON.

25:04.924 --> 25:08.127
WHY DON'T I GET ANOTHER DOCTOR
TO DO MARTY'S SURGERY?

25:08.127 --> 25:09.338
WHAT?!

25:11.631 --> 25:12.762
...A GOOD IDEA.

25:12.762 --> 25:14.764
YES.

25:14.764 --> 25:15.935
[ Chuckling ] YES.

25:15.935 --> 25:17.186
THANK YOU.

25:19.268 --> 25:20.730
LISTEN,
WE NEED THIS DEVICE.

25:20.730 --> 25:23.563
THIS WILL BUY THE KID TIME
UNTIL A HEART BECOMES AVAILABLE.

25:23.563 --> 25:25.855
THAT'S CRAP! YOU'RE THE FDA!
YOU MAKE THE RULES!

25:25.855 --> 25:27.737
I JUST SET
A BROKEN RADIUS

25:27.737 --> 25:30.279
AND ASSISTED
ON MANDIBULAR O.R.I.F.

25:30.279 --> 25:31.651
HOW GREAT IS THIS DAY?

25:31.651 --> 25:33.573
MM. MY KID'S TRAPPED IN A BUBBLE
FOR THE REST OF HIS LIFE.

25:33.573 --> 25:34.954
YOU AND BAILEY
WILL FIGURE IT OUT.

25:34.954 --> 25:36.325
THAT'S HOW GREAT
THIS DAY IS.

25:36.325 --> 25:38.828
IMAGINATION AND INNOVATION
ARE EVERYWHERE.

25:38.828 --> 25:40.870
I'M SEEING
A LOT OF MISERY AND FAILURE.

25:40.870 --> 25:41.871
ALEX.

25:41.871 --> 25:43.583
SHOULD I TAKE
THE PRIVATE-PRACTICE JOB?

25:43.583 --> 25:44.754
I THOUGHT
YOU'D ALREADY DECIDED

25:44.754 --> 25:46.295
THAT YOU WERE GONNA CALL
DR. BUTTHOLE AND --

25:46.295 --> 25:47.837
SO YANG'S WINNING AWARDS,
AND I'M SELLING OUT?

25:47.837 --> 25:49.548
YOU'RE NOT A SELLOUT
FOR TAKING A JOB

25:49.548 --> 25:50.880
DOING SOMETHING
THAT YOU LOVE.

25:50.880 --> 25:52.221
PRIVATE PRACTICE
WAS NEVER THE PLAN.

25:52.221 --> 25:53.843
IT WAS NEVER SUPPOSED TO BE
ABOUT THE MONEY.

25:53.843 --> 25:55.845
WELL, THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH MAKING MONEY.

25:55.845 --> 25:56.936
WHAT AM I GONNA BUY?

25:56.936 --> 25:58.347
A CONDO IN ASPEN?
I DON'T EVEN SKI.

25:58.347 --> 26:00.479
[ CHUCKLES ] NOT EVERYONE
WHO'S RICH IS AN ASS.

26:00.479 --> 26:02.521
YOU COULD TAKE THE JOB
AND NOT BE AN ASS.

26:04.944 --> 26:06.395
BRADEN?
David: BRADEN!

26:06.395 --> 26:08.357
BRADEN!
BRADEN, WHERE ARE YOU?!

26:08.357 --> 26:10.189
[ Sobbing ] WHERE IS HE?!
WHERE IS MY SON?!
WE CAN'T FIND HIM!

26:10.189 --> 26:11.240
BRADEN!

26:11.240 --> 26:12.742
WHOA! WHOA!
WATCH IT!

26:12.742 --> 26:13.903
[ Laughing ] WHOA!

26:13.903 --> 26:15.284
I'M GONNA GET YOU!
NO, YOU'RE NOT!

26:15.284 --> 26:17.076
Woman:
NO RUNNING IN THE HALL.

26:23.753 --> 26:25.665
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

26:25.665 --> 26:27.546
Woman: WHOA!

26:27.546 --> 26:29.548
I GOT YOU!
NO, YOU DIDN'T!

26:29.548 --> 26:30.549
YOU'RE TOTALLY IT.

26:30.549 --> 26:32.131
FRANKIE! DON'T TOUCH HIM!
BRADEN!

26:32.131 --> 26:33.342
YOU CAN'T.
HE'S IMMUNO-COMPROMISED.

26:33.342 --> 26:34.383
ANY MORE EXPOSURE --

26:34.383 --> 26:35.845
EVEN BREATHING ON HIM --
PUTS HIM AT RISK.

26:35.845 --> 26:36.846
[ SOBBING ]

26:36.846 --> 26:38.768
CAN EVERYONE
PLEASE STEP AWAY FROM THE BOY?

26:38.768 --> 26:40.139
[ PEOPLE MURMURING ]

26:54.613 --> 26:56.075
[ Sobbing ] MY LITTLE GUY.
OKAY, SON. DON'T WORRY.

26:56.075 --> 26:57.406
WE LOVE YOU SO.
IT'S OKAY, SON, ALL RIGHT?

26:57.406 --> 26:59.158
DON'T WORRY.
DON'T WORRY.

26:59.158 --> 27:02.041
WE'RE GONNA BE RIGHT HERE.
WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.
YOU'RE SO STRONG.

27:02.041 --> 27:03.412
DON'T WORRY.

27:03.412 --> 27:06.125
MOMMY AND DADDY
ARE HERE, OKAY?
WE'RE RIGHT HERE, SON.

27:06.125 --> 27:08.417
DON'T WORRY.

27:08.417 --> 27:11.550
BRADEN TOLD ME
HE WAS FINE.

27:11.550 --> 27:13.302
MOM...

27:13.302 --> 27:14.383
IS LINK GONNA DIE?

27:19.388 --> 27:21.560
I-I HOPE NOT.

27:21.560 --> 27:23.102
BUT HE'S REALLY SICK.

27:23.102 --> 27:24.393
HE'S EVEN WORSE
THAN IVY WAS,

27:24.393 --> 27:26.525
AND YOU REMEMBER
HOW BAD SHE WAS?

27:28.728 --> 27:29.819
WHAT?

27:29.819 --> 27:30.940
I HAVE SOME GOOD NEWS.

27:31.941 --> 27:33.612
Owen: IT WAS A NO.
IT WAS A HARD NO.

27:33.612 --> 27:35.614
AND THEN I REALIZED
THAT FRANKIE WAS RIGHT.

27:35.614 --> 27:37.156
YOU ARE
A BIG-TIME DOCTOR.

27:37.156 --> 27:39.538
SO I TOLD THEM THAT YOU WERE
ABOUT TO WIN A HARPER AVERY.

27:39.538 --> 27:41.580
THEY PLACED THE CARDIAC PUMPS
IN 10 SHEEP HEARTS,

27:41.580 --> 27:43.662
AND 9 OUT OF THE 10 WORKED
WITHOUT CLOTTING.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.204
IT'S BRILLIANT.

27:45.204 --> 27:47.496
THEY PUT ME ON HOLD AND THEN
CAME BACK A FEW MINUTES LATER

27:47.496 --> 27:49.128
AND SAID OKAY.

27:49.128 --> 27:51.711
JUST LIKE THAT -- BOOM.
SUDDENLY, YOU HAVE CLOUT.

27:51.711 --> 27:53.883
SUDDENLY,
YOU CAN GET THINGS DONE.

27:53.883 --> 27:55.214
USING THE SHEEP
WAS PERFECT.

27:55.214 --> 27:56.926
THEIR HEARTS ARE
ABOUT THE SAME SIZE AS LINK'S.

27:56.926 --> 27:58.057
PARENTS SIGNED CONSENT.

27:58.057 --> 27:59.508
THEY PUT THE DEVICE
ON THE NEXT PLANE.

27:59.508 --> 28:01.430
I GOT WILSON COORDINATING
WITH THE AIRLINES.

28:01.430 --> 28:03.933
HOW THE HELL DID YOU
TALK THE FDA INTO DOING THAT?

28:03.933 --> 28:06.265
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIVE THIS.

28:06.265 --> 28:08.567
OKAY. IT WAS A NO.
IT WAS A HARD NO. AND THEN --

28:08.567 --> 28:09.899
QUIET! PLEASE!

28:09.899 --> 28:12.481
I'VE GOT ABOUT FOUR HOURS TO
GET THROUGH ALL THEIR RESEARCH.

28:12.481 --> 28:14.073
CAN YOU PLEASE
TAKE THE PARTY OUTSIDE?

28:14.073 --> 28:15.274
Jo:
SAN FRANCISCO'S FOGGED IN.

28:15.274 --> 28:16.405
THEY'VE GROUNDED
ALL COMMERCIAL FLIGHTS

28:16.405 --> 28:17.907
FOR AT LEAST
ANOTHER COUPLE OF HOURS.

28:17.907 --> 28:19.238
WELL,
HE'S GETTING WORSE.

28:19.238 --> 28:21.620
I DON'T THINK THAT HE HAS
THAT KIND OF TIME.

28:21.620 --> 28:22.952
LET'S GO.

28:22.952 --> 28:25.034
ROSS WILL TRANSPORT THE KIDNEY
ONCE I TAKE IT OUT,

28:25.034 --> 28:26.705
AND THEN YOU'LL JOIN ME
FOR THE TRANSFER.

28:26.705 --> 28:28.587
ROGER THAT.

28:28.587 --> 28:29.879
YOU OKAY, ROSS?
YOU GOT THIS?

28:29.879 --> 28:31.460
Stephanie: ROSS!

28:31.460 --> 28:33.462
SWAP MONKEY. YOU CAN HAVE
YOUR CONDUITS BACK.

28:33.462 --> 28:35.885
Shane: I'M GOOD.
NO. HEY, UNH-UNH!
I CALLED SWAP MONKEY.

28:35.885 --> 28:37.676
DON'T YOU GO INTO THAT O.R.
DON'T YOU DARE!

28:37.676 --> 28:39.468
TOO LATE!

28:39.468 --> 28:41.510
DAMN IT, ROSS.

28:41.510 --> 28:42.551
[ SIGHS ]

28:42.551 --> 28:43.602
HI.

28:43.602 --> 28:44.804
I WAS --

28:45.805 --> 28:47.346
NEVER MIND.

28:48.607 --> 28:51.150
Richard:
W-WHAT'S A SWAP MONKEY?

28:51.150 --> 28:54.693
IT'S WHEN YOU WANT
WHAT SOMEONE ELSE HAS.

28:54.693 --> 28:56.655
SAN JOSE AIRPORT'S OPEN.
THERE'S A FLIGHT THAT
CONNECTS THROUGH PORTLAND.

28:56.655 --> 28:57.777
IT CAN BE HERE
IN SIX HOURS.

28:57.777 --> 28:59.278
THAT'S STILL TOO LONG.

28:59.278 --> 29:00.619
I'M TELLING YOU, PRIVATE CHARTER
IS THE ONLY WAY THIS WILL WORK.

29:00.619 --> 29:01.530
YEAH, RICHIE RICH,
YOU SAID THAT.

29:01.530 --> 29:03.122
I GOT ONE!
A-A PRIVATE JET.

29:03.122 --> 29:05.124
IT'S FUELED AND READY
AND ON THE TARMAC OR WHATEVER.

29:05.124 --> 29:06.916
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH!
OKAY! OKAY! GET IT!
GET IT, GET IT, GET IT!

29:06.916 --> 29:09.248
YES, VERY INTERESTED.
WHAT WOULD --

29:09.248 --> 29:10.419
It's $25,000.

29:10.419 --> 29:11.580
[ SIGHS ]
OH.

29:11.580 --> 29:12.832
SO, WHO PAYS FOR THAT?

29:12.832 --> 29:14.463
NO, WE NEED BOARD APPROVAL
FOR THAT ONE.

29:14.463 --> 29:15.374
YOU'RE THE BOARD!

29:15.374 --> 29:16.505
WELL, YOU CALL
AN EMERGENCY BOARD MEETING

29:16.505 --> 29:17.676
BECAUSE WE HAVE TO!
COME ON!

29:17.676 --> 29:18.717
WE GOT TO DO IT!

29:18.717 --> 29:19.929
JUST USE THIS, OKAY?

29:19.929 --> 29:21.220
PUT IT ON MY CARD.

29:21.220 --> 29:23.512
I'LL SORT IT OUT
WITH THE BOARD LATER. IT'S FINE.

29:23.512 --> 29:25.184
[ SIGHS ]
THANK YOU, JACKSON.

29:25.184 --> 29:27.016
YEAH, THANKS.

29:27.016 --> 29:28.477
Jo: OKAY, AMEX.

29:28.477 --> 29:31.100
3768...

29:31.100 --> 29:33.562
IT WAS THE NIGHT THAT U-DUB
MADE IT INTO THE FINALS.

29:33.562 --> 29:35.604
THIS [CHUCKLES]
POOR FRESHMAN FELL

29:35.604 --> 29:37.196
WHEN BLOCKING
A THREE-POINTER.

29:37.196 --> 29:38.567
IT WAS
SUCH A FREAK INJURY.

29:38.567 --> 29:40.569
THE TIBIA WAS SHATTERED
IN TWO PLACES,

29:40.569 --> 29:44.573
THE BONE WAS STICKING OUT
LIKE 6 INCHES FROM THE SKIN.

29:44.573 --> 29:46.035
IT WAS
TOTALLY DISGUSTING.

29:46.035 --> 29:48.908
BUT I ASSISTED THE ATTENDING
IN THE O.R.,

29:48.908 --> 29:50.960
PLACING THE ROD
AND THE SCREWS.

29:50.960 --> 29:52.671
IT PROBABLY TOOK
LIKE SEVEN HOURS.

29:52.671 --> 29:54.964
I FELL IN LOVE.

29:54.964 --> 29:57.756
IT WAS ORTHO
ALL THE WAY.

29:57.756 --> 29:59.548
[ COMPUTER BUZZING ]

29:59.548 --> 30:01.881
Yeah, look, Callie,
I know you don't want
to hear this, but --

30:01.881 --> 30:03.382
OH, COME ON! NOTHING?

30:03.382 --> 30:05.384
A lot of people
are depressed.

30:05.384 --> 30:06.515
I'm a happy person!

30:06.515 --> 30:09.558
I HAVE A NUMBER FOR YOU.
THIS GUY'S GREAT.

30:09.558 --> 30:11.100
HE HELPED ME THROUGH
A REALLY DIFFICULT TIME.

30:11.100 --> 30:12.101
My life is perfect.

